Dow climbs 138 points on gains for shares of Boeing, Merck

The Dow Jones Industrial Average is climbing Thursday morning with shares of Boeing and Merck delivering the strongest returns for the blue-chip average. The Dow DJIA, -0.69% is trading 138 points higher (0.5%), as shares of Boeing BA, -0.94% and Merck MRK, -0.28% are contributing to the index's intraday rally. Boeing's shares have risen $4.63, or 3.1%, while those of Merck are up $2.33, or 3.0%, combining for an approximately 48-point bump for the Dow. Also contributing significantly to the gain are Raytheon Technologies Corp. RTX, 1.75%, Procter & Gamble PG, -0.02%, and Pfizer PFE, 0.14%. A $1 move in any of the benchmark's 30 components equates to a 6.86-point swing.

